	   <tr><td colspan=2>There was a sweet GM event this past weekend in EK..lots of spectres (graveyard knights) wandering around.&nbsp;&nbsp;I looted this off of a knight I killed and just about woke up my friends by cheering. =) First GM event and all that I actually got something.  Event was named Graveyard of the Dead.  This belt certainly helps my WIS-poor druid. (My first EQ character and I had no idea what to put points into, so my base WIS is 98). I think I'm doing OK, I'm non-twinked with 163 WIS now at 39th.  People tell me I'm useless because I'll never be able to quad-kite, but to them I say Bah!  =) Soloing bores me, I'd rather interact with a group of people, it is much more fun.<br><br>Walk safe everyone, and if you see me, say hi =)<br><br>Ceinnoni Proudfoot<br>Halfling druid of the 39th season<br>Prima Nocturnae, MT server<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
