	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hehe well i just got this girdle today at a GM Event on Bristlebane in WC. Werewolves were all over. Was lotsa fun for me since all but the Greater Werewolves were green to me, the Greater ones were dark blue. I also ended up getting the exp for killing the Werewolf Overlord (lvl 55 mob) but nothing dropped off him that I couild use. Was quite a fun event and I came out with three items. As to your wisdom problems try this on for size... I started this char with 75 wis, which is the lowest you can start with I think lol, like you this was my first char and I didn't know any better, but now at lvl 53 I have my wis at 200 finally hehe. One thing that helps me out is I keep Misty Thicket Picnics and Qeynos Afternoon Tea on me almost all the time, except during raids. I get an extra 10 wis from them. Quad kiting with low wis is quite possible I can tell you that it's just not quite as easy as it could be =). There is plenty of wis gear out there, even if some is rather hard to obtain, all it takes is some dedication and time, or in some cases just a lot of pp =P anyway this is a pretty nice mid lvl belt and I'll probably use it for a while. Obviously not an uber item but hey it was dropped off mobs that even a lvl 24 druid could've killed without too much trouble. That is if they weren't KSed geez you shoulda seen the mayhem in the zone... anyway I'm rambling gratz to everybody who managed to get one of these.<br><br>Mfcox lvl 53 Druid of Karana<br>Bristlebane Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
